    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-22T23:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-22T23:16:00-05:00" n="430"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/657</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-23T00:00:00-04:16">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1917, 12 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3.25 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My April 25, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d430fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_264">p. 264</ref>.</note> I am
                    reliably informed that congress of neutrals will be called for August 15. <hi
                        rend="italic">La Prensa</hi> to-day says that the principal matters of the
                    program of the conference will be announced soon and that Bolivia, Brazil,
                    Colombia, Chile, Mexico, Paraguay, Peru, Uruguay, Ecuador, Haiti, and the five
                    Central American States adhered to the initiative but since their so answering
                    Argentina, Haiti [omission]; that only United States of America, Cuba, and
                    Panama did not agree to the idea, who have also declared war, Dominica, which
                    has broken relations with Germany, and Venezuela.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
